  "text": "where δH PLA,m is PLA's enthalpy of fusion, δH PLA,cc is the enthalpy corresponding to cold crystallization, δH PLA,m,• is the enthalpy of fusion when the polyester is in a 100% crystalline state (δH PLA,m,• = 93.6 J/g) [CITATION_1] , and W PLA is the mass fraction of PLA in the mixture. The X c of PLA is indicated in the right-most column in Table 1 ; it decreases from 33.8% for pure PLA to 17.3% for L80V20.",
